Package base_SOM_Objects.som_examples

Class SOM_Example

java.lang.Object
base_SOM_Objects.som_examples.base.baseDataPtVis
base_SOM_Objects.som_examples.SOM_Example
Direct Known Subclasses:
SOM_GeomObj, SOM_MapNode
public abstract class SOM_Example extends baseDataPtVis
NOTE : None of the data types in this file are thread safe so do not allow for opportunities for concurrent modification of any instanced object in this file. This decision was made for speed concerns - concurrency-protected objects have high overhead that proved greater than any gains in 10 execution threads. All multithreaded access of these objects should be designed such that any individual object is only accessed by a single thread. This is the base class describing an example data point to be used to train a SOM
Author:
john turner

If category is not used, null category should be supported by consuming functions. THIS SHOULD ONLY BE USED WHEN THIS EXAMPLE IS A TRAINING EXAMPLE; OTHERWISE SHOULD BE ABLE TO RETURN NULL

    • setTrainingExBMU

      public final void setTrainingExBMU(SOM_MapNode _n, int _ftrType)
      this adds the passed node as this _training_ example's best matching unit on the map - this is used for -training- examples having been set as bmus by the SOM executable, hence why it uses the full distance and does not exclude zero features in this example; also does not use comparison vector but actual ftrMaps/training vector for the above reason this also adds this data point to the map's node with a key of the distance
      Parameters:
      _n - bmu for this example
      _ftrType - type of features used for comparison (unnormalized, normed per feature across all data, normed per example)

    • buildCompFtrVector

      public abstract void buildCompFtrVector(float _ratio)
      this will build the comparison feature vector array that is used as the comparison vector in distance measurements - for most cases this will just be a copy of the ftr vector array but in some instances, there might be an alternate vector to be used to handle when, for example, an example has ftrs that do not appear on the map
      Parameters:
      _ratio - ratio of features to secondary features calculated to use to build comparison vector
